The paper proposes a data fusion pipeline based on computer vision techniques, including a novel inpainting algorithm with soft masking, for precipitation nowcasting. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of neural networks for precipitation nowcasting suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also involves the fusion of radar and satellite observations, which suggests that it may belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The use of computer vision techniques for data fusion suggests that the paper may also belong to the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks for precipitation nowcasting suggests that the paper may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
